article.headline: Eagles outrebound Syracuse 41-22
article.linkText: Boston College crushes Syracuse in first round
article.story:
HARTFORD, Connecticut(Ticker) -- Jessalyn Deveny scored 14 
points to lead No. 25 Boston College to a 64-36 triumph over
Syracuse in the first round of the Big East tournament.

Deveny scored 10 points in the first half, including a pair of
3-pointers, and finished 5-of-10 from the floor for the Eagles
(22-6), who led 36-18 at halftime after closing out the first
half with a 16-2 run.

Deveny also collected seven rebounds as Boston College dominated
the Orangewomen on the glass, 41-22.

Guard Amber Jacobs hit two 3-pointers and added 13 points, and
Aja Parham chipped in with eight points and five boards off the
bench for the Eagles, who will face Miami in the Big East
tournament quarterfinals on Sunday afternoon.

Boston College, which had nine of its 11 players score, produced
25 points off of 17 Syracuse turnovers, including four steals
by Brooke Queenan.

Chineze Nwagbo paced the Orangewomen (6-21), scoring 11 points
and collecting seven rebounds.

Julie McBride added eight points, but hit just 3-of-14 shots
from the floor during a tough game for Syracuse, which shot
under 30 percent in the contest.
